                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/3252a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moore</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-01-18T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 18, 1929—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7. I wish you would find out what the Government of Peru is willing to do to make
                    a settlement. As you know, it is useless to talk of turning the city of Arica
                    over to Peru. They have always understood that it could not be done. If there is
                    to be a settlement, I should like to have it accomplished before I go out of
                    office, and the time is very short.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
